HEADWORD: Datolite
<hw>Dat"o*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From. Gr.
<ets><grk>date`omai</grk></ets> to divide + <ets>-lite</ets>; in
allusion to the granular structure of a massive variety.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A borosilicate of lime commonly occurring in
glassy,, greenish crystals.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>datholite</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

